Batch edit stages multiple operations across symbols and files, then applies them atomically in one write. Apply returns an error if validation fails — no need to preview first.

Prefer batch edits for 2+ operations. For a single change, use the Edit tool directly. Stage all related edits first, then apply together with `rm {{ paths.edit_staged_diff() }}`. This is safe (tree-sitter validated) and efficient (one atomic write).

Writing to a staging endpoint stages the edit directly — no prior read required. Repeated writes to the same endpoint stage more operations. Stage edits with the `Write` tool.

